NFL, Pepsi to Announce $2.3 Billion Sponsorship Extension, WSJ Reports

-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 
2011-09-06T04:01:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/nfl-pepsi-to-announce-2-3-billion-sponsorship-extension-wsj-reports.html
PepsiCo Inc., the world’s largest
snack-food maker, agreed to a 10-year extension of its
sponsorship accord with the  National Football League  that may be
worth $2.3 billion, the Wall Street Journal reported.  The deal, through the 2022 playoffs, may be announced
today, the Journal said, citing an unidentified person with
knowledge of the contract’s details.  The accord ensures PepsiCo brands including Gatorade,
Pepsi, Frito-Lay, Tropicana and Quaker Oats remain official
marketing partners of the league at a cost of almost $100
million a year, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dex McLuskey in Dallas  at
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net . 